This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, specifically in the context of tournament rules. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the manipulation of tournaments, which involves strategic decision-making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also uses probability theory and statistical analysis to evaluate the manipulability of different tournament rules, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different tournament rules, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
